ENTRY            F0822   20251227   20260311   20260311       F107
SUBENT        F0822001   20251227   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                  9         28
TITLE      Elastic and inelastic scattering of 30 MeV
           alpha-particles on even isotopes of palladium
AUTHOR     (V.Riech,R.Scherwinski,G.Lindstrom,E.Fretwurst,
           K.Gridnev,P.P.Zarubin,R.Kolalis)
INSTITUTE  (2GERHAM,4RUSSUL)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,542,61,1992)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,2GERHAM)
DETECTOR   (SI) The angular distributions were measured with three
           detectors, mounted on a coolable turntable, in the
           angular range 10-120 degr.
SAMPLE     Self-supporting target foils with thickness of
           300-700 ug/cm2, which were fabricated from isotopically
           enriched material, have been used.
                                Enrichment (in %)
                   102Pd 104Pd 105Pd 106Pd 108Pd 110Pd Thickness
                                                         ug/cm2
           104Pd   0.15  95.25 2.64  1.23  0.54  0.19     318
           106Pd   <0.02 0.13  0.79  98.48 0.48  0.12     694
           108Pd   <0.01 0.07  0.27  0.95  98.35 0.36     639
           110Pd   <0.01 0.12  0.36  0.46  1.32  97.73    530
ERR-ANALYS The cross sections of the most prominent states are
           inaccurate to about +-5%, mainly due to the target-
           thickness determination. In cases of small absolute
           cross-sections statistics, unidentified target
           contaminations and background fluctuations contribute
           as well.
HISTORY    (20070306C)
           (20251227U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              28
COMMON               2          3
EN         ERR-DIG
MEV        PER-CENT
       30.5         1.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           35
